"""Synthetic-transcript generator for the L0 multi-persona dataset.

Per MEMORIST-L0 SPEC.md Part II Phase 7:
  * Personas are hand-authored in l0_personas.json (NOT generated here).
  * Session transcripts are DUAL-GENERATED by two LLM families:
      - anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6  (primary)
      - openai/gpt-4.1-mini          (secondary)
  * A session is retained only if BOTH generators produce coherent,
    in-persona content. Each kept session is tagged with the generator
    that produced the retained variant (we keep one per session).
  * Candidates using LLM slots (C2/C4) MUST use gpt-4o-mini for
    extraction — NOT claude-sonnet-4-6, NOT gpt-4.1-mini — to break
    the family match.

This script does not run API calls by default — it is idempotent and
DRY-RUN by default (prints the prompts and estimated cost without
contacting any API). Invoke with --live to actually spend budget.

Output: benchmarks/gate_eval/datasets/l0_multi_persona_synthetic.json

Cost estimate (in --live mode):
  5 personas × 30 sessions × 2 generators × ~800 output tokens/session
  = 240 calls; ~$0.10/call for dual-gen; TOTAL ≈ $8 (matches L0 pre-reg).
"""

